Version control is a crucial aspect of software development that helps teams and individuals manage changes to their codebase efficiently. It allows developers to track alterations, collaborate seamlessly, and revert to previous states when needed. One of the most popular version control systems is Git.

What is Version Control?
Version control, also known as source control or revision control, is a system that records changes to files over time. It enables developers to keep track of modifications, maintain a history of their work, and collaborate with others without chaos.

